body:
This PR adds two sets of vertex smearing parameters:
- `Realistic50ns13TeVCollisionZeroTesla`: it contains the values computed from Run2015A luminous region with 0T data and alignment for first collisions (see #10222 );
- `Realistic50ns13TeVCollision`: it contains the values computed from Run2015B luminous region with 3.8T data and PCL-like alignment (see #10384 ). The `sigmaZ` value is still set to the "original" value of 5.3 cm, while 2015B data indicate that it is actually shrunk to ~4.3 cm: it is pending discussion with LHC OP.
